claims:
16. A method of treatment of ischemia in a patient comprising:
isolating a population of menstrual blood-derived stem cells;
incubating the population of menstrual blood-derived stem cells, such that the population of menstrual blood-derived stem cells excrete at least one trophic factor selected from the group consisting of vascular endothelial growth factor, brain-derived neurotrophic factor, and neurotrophin-3;
collecting the excreted at least one trophic factor; and
administering the at least one trophic factor into the patient.
